5 Dinner here made for a great evening.  The views from almost anywhere in the restuarant are excellent.  You can look out on the strip, specifically Wynn/Encore and Venetian/Palazzo.  Our server Marc was great.  From the second we sat down until the second we left he was on top of everything.  This level of service is what pushed my rating up from a four star to a five star.  The bread they bring out is great.  There is an option for everyone.  We chose to do the wine tasting.  For only $25 you get to taste several great wines.  This is a great deal and i recomend it for anyone that enjoys wine.  It is only offered seasonally though.  I ordered the dry aged steak au poivre with a courvoisier cream sauce.  I orderd it medium rare.  It came out cooked exactly as ordered.  It is amazing that so few places get this part right.  The crushed black pepper crust gives the meat a nice spice.  The cream sauce helps smooth it out.  They make a great combination.  For a side we ordered au gratin potatos.  They are terrific.  The portion is huge.  Easily split between 2 to 4 people.  There is plenty of cheese and the homemade chip crust gives them a great texture contrast.  The wife ordered the chop salad.  It looked great and she said it tasted even better.  This is more expensive than the average meal, but the service alone makes it worth every penny.
