3 We picked the Capital Grill for our special occassion dinner based on reviews and ratings on Yelp, etc. We started with drinks in the bar and the service was excellent. Pam, our mixologist, made us feel welcome and provided excellent libations. When we were seated, our dissappointment began. We had made reservations three weeks in advance and had requested a table at the corner window. When seated we were told that table was saved for a large party. O.K., so the table we were seated at had two of us with our backs to the view of the strip (a supposed highlight of this establishment) and the table was very small for our party of four. This proved to be more than the case as our appetizers were served. With the bread basket, butter, side plates, etc. there was barely room to set a water glass. Also, the air conditioning was on full blast and to the staff's credit, they did turn it off after we mentioned it. Three of us in the party ordered steaks and they were all delicious although all were cooked sllightly more well done than ordered. Our fourth ordered the salmon special and reported it was perfect. The side dishes did leave a lot to be desired. Two of us had the lobster bisque and it was just average to say the least. Not the rich bisque you would expect to find at this caliber of restaurant. The onion soup was satisfactory and the wedge salad was ample although the bleu cheese dressing was only so-so, again not what was expected. The waiter did not offer ground pepper at any servings. We ordered three side dishes, the famous mac, cheese & lobster (not very flavorful), the au gratin potatoes (burnt crust on the top) and asparagus (done just right). We ordered a bottle of wine with dinner and our waiter was prompt at keeping our glasses full. Overall, for a special occassion we were all a bit dissappointed in our overall experience. For the prices paid, the food should have been far superior to what we recieved and the overall service a bit higher standard. I doubt we will return with so many great restaurants available in Las Vegas.
